'''Glasses''' were optical instruments consisting of a frame holding a pair of lenses for improving [[eye]]sight. Some glasses were held in place by hand, like the pair occasionally used by [[Nuvo Vindi]];<ref name="Blue Shadow Virus" /> other models had arms which rested over the [[ear]]s, like the ones worn by some [[Unidentified Vyndal species|natives]] of [[Vyndal]].<ref name="The Fake Jedi">{{RebelsMagCite|3|The Fake Jedi}}</ref> [[Inspector]] [[Thanoth]] of the [[Galactic Empire]] often wore a [[monocle]] over his left eye during the [[Imperial Era]].<ref name="Darth Vader 8" /> During a meeting with [[Arihnda Pryce]], the [[Chiss]] [[Mitth'raw'nuruodo]] wore glasses in order to disguise his [[Color|red]] eyes so that others would believe him to be a [[Pantoran]].<ref name="Thrawn">[[Thrawn (novel)|''Thrawn'']]</ref>

{{Stub}}

==Behind the scenes==
Although [[George Lucas]] did not want eyeglasses to be present in his films,<ref name="Hyp">{{Hyperspace|url=hyperspace/member/postnotes/news20041124.html|series=Episode III Post Notes|text=Part of the Coruscant Elite}}</ref> such devices have nonetheless appeared in other [[canon]] sources such as "[[Blue Shadow Virus (episode)|Blue Shadow Virus]]" of [[The Clone Wars: Season One|''The Clone Wars'': Season One]]<ref name="Blue Shadow Virus" /> and "[[Double Agent Droid]]," the nineteenth episode of the animated television series ''[[Star Wars Rebels]]''{{'}} [[Star Wars Rebels Season Three|third season]].<ref name="Double Agent Droid" />

